[MIM: Motif Independet Metric - Luca Pinello]

[INSTALLATION AND REQUIREMENTS]

In order to use the MIM software you need:

python 2.7(http://www.python.org/getit/) 

and the following modules:

-numpy (http://sourceforge.net/projects/numpy/files/NumPy/1.6.1/)
-scipy (http://sourceforge.net/projects/scipy/files/scipy/0.9.0/)

[USAGE]

The program take in input a proper BED file (http://genome.ucsc.edu/FAQ/FAQformat.html#format1) that contains the coordinate on some genome of reference

The fasta file of your genome of reference (http://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/downloads.html)

To launch the program from a shell type:

python mim.py bed_file.bed /path_to_your_genome_directory/

The program will report the MIM value for the sequence extracted from the bed file and its p-value.